"Thread.sleep" should not be used in tests
Using Thread.sleep in a test is just generally a bad idea. It creates brittle tests that can fail unpredictably depending on environment ("Passes on my machine!") or load. Donâ€™t rely on timing (use mocks) or use libraries such as Awaitility for asynchroneous testing. 
